{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6901a","heading":"Congressional findings: used oil recycling","label":"6901a Congressional findings: used oil recycling","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch82/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6901a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Used Oil Re­cycling Act of 1980, and not as part of the Solid Waste Disposal Act which comprises this chapter."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6901a%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"used oil is a valuable source of increasingly scarce energy and materials;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6901a%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"technology exists to re-refine, reprocess, reclaim, and otherwise recycle used oil;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6901a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6901a%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"used oil constitutes a threat to public health and the environment when reused or disposed of improperly; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
